Bedtools is intended to run in a “command line” environment on UNIX, LINUX and Apple OS X operating systems. 
There are specific processes during the 4CseqR pipeline where we are using bedtools:

#Run bedtools "getfastsa" in order to get the fasta file format from bed file format 
bedtools getfasta -fi arabidopsis.fas -bed fragment_endsAllChrAGATCT100length.bed -fo fragment_endsAllChrAGATCT100length.fa


#Run the bedtools sort
bedtools sort -i results1_5_100leng.bed > results1_5_100leng_sorted.bed

#Run the bedtools intersect 
 bedtools intersect -a fragments_AthalianaAGATCTAllChrBlind100lenghtdelcol.bed -b results1_6_100leng_sorted.bed -wa -wb > intersect1_6leng100.txt

The above result from bedtools is the input to puthon script which merges and finaly creates the input for normalization

#Run the python script 
python merge_4Cnew2.py intersect1_3leng100.txt> finaltable1_3leng100.csv

